In a bowl, mix oil, vinegar, garlic, capers, and shrimp. Cover and chill, stirring occasionally, at least 30 minutes or up to 1 day. Trim ends from baguette and cut remaining bread crosswise into 36 equal slices. Set slices on racks on a 14- by 17-inch baking sheet. Bake in a 425 degrees F oven until golden, 6 to 8 minutes. If making ahead, store cool slices airtight up to 4 hours. Seed and finely chop tomato. Add tomato, bell pepper, and onion to shrimp mixture. Season with salt to taste. Spread cheese on toast. Place vegetables and 1 shrimp on each piece.